    boardPearls: ['Tinnitus: one of the earliest symptoms of salicylate toxicity (serum level ~20-30 mg/dL). Dose-related, fully reversible. The first symptom most patients notice.','Pulmonary edema in salicylate toxicity: non-cardiogenic (ARDS-like). Mechanism: increased pulmonary capillary permeability. Treat with oxygenation and HD — diuretics are not effective and may worsen volume depletion.','Differential: salicylate toxicity vs other anion-gap metabolic acidoses (MUDPILES: Methanol, Uremia, DKA, Propylene glycol, Isoniazid, Lactic acidosis, Ethylene glycol, Salicylates). Also causes mixed acid-base: respiratory alkalosis + anion gap metabolic acidosis.']
